Linux is a family of free and open-source software operating systems built around the Linux kernel. 
There are several Linux distributions like Ubuntu, Cent OS & Fedora. In the mentioned Linux distributions, there is a Graphical User Interface (GUI) and a  Command Line Interface (CLI). Here we will focus on the CLI presuming that is why you are here.

As a person who interacts with computers daily, knowing a couple of commands may make your life a little fancier. 

1. To know the folder you are operating in enter 'pwd' command.
2. To get the files are in that folder enter 'ls' command. For more details you can enter these commands 'ls -a' or 'ls -l'.
3. Changing to another directory enter 'cd' command.
4. For the Size of the folder use command 'du -h'.
5. To create a new folder enter 'mkdir' command followed by the name of the folder like 'mkdir file1'
6. To run commands enter 'sudo'. Like 'sudo ls' you will be prompted to enter the password inorder to complete the request made.
7. To get a list of all the files or folders including the hidden ones in that given folder enter the command 'du'.
8. To know the size of each file or folder enter 'du -h' command.

To get help incase you are stuck with a command, use the 'man' command. Man stands for manual. It will list the details of how yo use a given command like 'man cd' which displays the man page about cd.
